com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.data
Interface NativeFloat

All Superinterfaces:
NativeCapable, NativeFieldContainer, NativeNumber, NativePrimitive, NativeSingleFieldContainer
public interface NativeFloat
extends NativeNumber

The NativeFloat is the interface implemented by native capable classes wrapping a float value.

The framework has an internal class implementing this interface.

If native the corresponding native memory is a float (jfloat), a Java reference of this type can be considered like a jfloat* native variable.

This interface is used when using the expression "float*" with the method NativeVarTypeManager.dec(String).

Author:
Jose M. Arranz Santamaria

Method Detail

getFloatValue

float getFloatValue(int fetchMode)
Returns the internal float value synchronized with the native memory if instance is native using the specified fetch mode.

Fetch values FAST, EMBEDDED and DEEP have the same behavior: native memory is read and internal value is synchronized before return.

Parameters:
fetchMode - the fetch mode.
Returns:
the internal float value.
See Also:
Fetch

setFloatValue

void setFloatValue(float value,
                   int unFetchMode)
Sets the internal float value synchronizing the native memory with the new value if instance is native using the specified "unfetch" mode.

Unfetch values FAST, EMBEDDED and DEEP have the same behavior: native memory is updated with the new value.

Parameters:
value - the new value.
unFetchMode - the "unfetch" mode.
